OL,6,FNo programme featuring Edwards should
OL,7,Fever be seen again.
OL,9,FBut what about clips of the moments of
OL,10,Fhistoric importance which he anchored?
OL,12,FFrom the unfolding horror of September
OL,13,F11 to the opening of the London
OL,14,FOlympics and the death of the Queen
OL,15,Fand the Coronation of the new King, he
OL,16,Fis part of the story of our times.
OL,18,FThis is a tricky one.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/7
